body.description: END OF THE BATTLE, START OF THE WARSuspecting the oni princess who ruled over the defeated Chimera Clausen was the offspring of a high-level demon, Mira entrusts Kagura with the investigation. Meanwhile, the pint-sized summoner returns to Solomon to make her report…and get a little R&R with Mariana! But when the investigation reveals the demon mastermind is now after the Oni’s Sealed Casket, Mira, along with three other Wise Men, must rush to thwart the enemy’s schemes once again…

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great story with good artwork
reviews.reviewText: I'm so excited to be able to continue on with this story! Comedy and adventure a great combo with fantastic artwork. Now waiting on Vol. 10 to come out in December......feels so long away lol

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not the best read of the series, but entertaining enough
reviews.reviewText: Volume 9 is for the most part about tying up some loose ends from the previous arc, lot of talking but with a bit of action near the end. Mira faces little challenge, but her interactions with others are entertaining enough. Of course, there is the occasional (ecchi) cringe, but that should not come as a surprise this far into the series. All in all, not the best read of the series, but entertaining enough.
